caption: They literally saved us during the pandemic they were one of very few places that remained open and they kept the practices safe. The food is really good and I've tried a lot of Indian food, the service is fast and the prices are reasonable.
love this place awesome food!

I go to this nice place many times a year! This is my favorite restaurant to pass a nice evening.  I go there many times. The food is excellent, the staff is friendly and the prices are good. I like eating in this place to have a decent supper.
Their food is consistently exceptionally delicious.

I arrive at this outstanding restaurant many times  as I like the good air that is outline this place. The personel is exceptionally loyal and professional. The service is remarkablywonderfully fast. Most important, the food they serve is good. I ate there often and I was always delighted. The price is reasobable. I recommend this place to all my friends.

I had ordered several items on their menu for our office party. Ms. Suchi (owner) was the one who took my orders and she was very kind, generous and helped me choose the vegan items from their menu. Despite having a limited budget, she gave me a discount and was able to accommodate all my requests. They delivered my orders on time, the portions were huge and everyone at the party ENJOYED and were SATISFIED with the delicious entrees that Kanan restaurant provided. To Ms. Suchi and the staff at Kanan, I extend my sincerest gratitude for making our party a memorable one.
Every one of our 4 dishes was excellent.  Vindaloo was hot but so flavorful

I have been searching for a good Indian place since moving to NYC and I finally found it!!!! Kanan is great for vegan, vegetarians and meat eaters alike. Plus, they are currently running a phenomenal take out special for only $13 that includes a appetizer, entree, rice and naan -- it doesn't get better than that! I definitely highly recommend Kanan and am so glad I found it!!

We just ordered from Kanan for the first time and loved it. The lamb raan was delicious, flavorful and tender. Also had aloo saagwala, potatoes and spinach-delicious. Will definitely be back for more!
Ordered from here 2 days ago and we all got sick to our stomachs! Only ordered veggie dishes and didn't expect to get sick from that!  Will not be ordering from here anytime soon!
Nice staff, great food. Order mild spice if it's your first time!
Would surely recommend eating here. Fantastic character, yummy dishes, good customer service. Great work.
Food good. Service is quick

We love to go out. Last night we  visited this fine restaurant which friends recommended to us. We passed a beautiful time there with superb meal and a well-trained stuff and a talented cook. We  added this restaurant in our phone list  and we shall no doubt return very soon. We highly recommend.

The restaurant is extraordinary and broad, the food was enchanting and the prices were very reasonable. rapidly, effective service and very attentive staff. I recommend this place.

This place has really great food and great prices. I ordered food from here many times and it’s always very fresh and delivered hot. Today there was an issue with the delivery and they took very good care of me and sent me another order for free! Thank you.
Excellent restaurant. I order all the time and always delicious and on time!

Quick service. Very reasonably priced if 3 or more people. Gravy quantity could have been more. Kachori chaat was very home like. Saag paneer was not with pureed spinach gravy but still tasted good. Malai kofta was very sweet, even though I usually like sweet gravies. Bread basket was filling and all breads were well made. All gravies come with rice, so that was a good unexpected surprise .

Don't let the  humble storefront and lack of ambience fool you. The quality of food is excellent. Dishes are flavorful, not salty or greasy. Portions are big and price is reasonable for the quality and portion size. I had a chicken biryani entree which was thoughtfully prepared with many spices, and included golden raisins, onions and other nice touches which added to the flavor complexity without overpowering.  My ground lamb kabob appetizer was big enough to be a whole meal in itself, and also perfectly seasoned and grilled just right.  Mango lassi was refreshing and sweet enough without going overboard. Garlic naan was deliciously garlicky.  I'll be back next time I'm in Brooklyn!
Ordered takeout via seamless. Had the chicken tika, samosas, bindhi, naan and more. We were looking for a solid Indian place in the neighborhood and we'll definitely be ordering again.
Food was amazing
Small, cozy atmosphere with friendly, attentive service. While not the flashiest restaurant in Brooklyn, Kanan served up the best lamb curry I've ever tasted. Highly recommended.

I love the take out delivery deal! everything is so good, fresh, authentic and the staff is beyond nice.  GET THE BUTTER CHICKEN  Love this restaurant and eat there at least once a month....or more :)
Food is awesome. Half off most entrees during lunch hours. BYOB!!
It is a good place with great Indian food. The staff is friendly and I'll be back to try other dishes.
The food is pretty cheap, but you get what you paid for.

Awful. I would give this place zero stars if I could. Ordered the Aloo Gobi which was too salty, and on the menu it states - with or without peas. When I ordered it on seamless there was no option to choose with peas or without. I don't know if this is the restaurants's fault, or seamless's but regardless, it was way too salty. Chicken samosas were flavorless and not spiced. At all. Just plain ground chicken and nothing else. No raita included, and the green sauce tasted like straight vinegar, while the tamarind sauce was far too sweet. My naan tasted stale. No utensils or straws included. Lassi, which was definitely not made with fresh mango and came from a pre- made mix... was dark orange and clearly artificially colored, spilled because they placed it in the paper bag sideways!! . I threw my entire order away. Will not be ordering from here again.
Friendly staff. Excellent food. Will def go back

Nice food, service and good prices.
Great Indian takeouts, especially 13.99 deal!  Highly recommend if you are in the area.

Great service. Quick. Sooo delicious. Restaurant has child seat (and it isn't broken) which was a big plus for me. Went on a Sunday and had no idea entrees were 50% off. Generous portions.

Best Indian in the slope!

Tasted great.  We had chicken tikka masala and paneer saagwala.  Really good.  Cheapest meal we had in Brooklyn.  Open til 11 pm which is an added bonus. Quick bite after a show at the Bell House.  Definitely recommend!

Delivery is super fast, the quality is always good. The food tends to err on the spicy side (which is great for those like me who love spice and bad for people like my wife who are sensitive to spicy food). I ordered Chicken Tika Masala  (normally very mild), but there was definitely a level of spice to it. I also ordered the Chicken Vindaloo, and it was off the charts...I was on another planet.  The staff is always friendly and patient. This is a fantastic addition to the Gowanus area.

My girlfriend and I just attempted to eat our meal from here, but it is probably the worst indian food I have had in New York. It's really unfortunate that our $30 meal was not worth it.  We ordered daal Turka, naan, rice, tandoori chicken, and 2 drinks. When the meal was delivered the drinks had been forgotten.  The daal was very bland. There was no flavor and it was very watery. There was hardly any lentils in it.  The naan was soggy and the texture was just very off.  The tandoori chicken was decent, but still below the standard of many other indian places I've tried.  My girlfriend and I spent 4 months in India, and while we didn't expect the same quality as we had over there, we expected an indian run restaurant to be able to satisfy our craving. This was unfortunately not the case.  Worst $30 I've spent in a long time.

One of the rare exceptions to the "Indian food is lousy in Park Slope" rule. Great food, spice is appropriate, delivery on time, bread arrives fresh and warm ... careful: their Makhani (butter chicken) is highly addictive!
Fantastic Indian food at last! try everything! I'm addicted to their spicy Vindaloo and Poori.

Easily the best Indian restaurant in a two mile radius.  Granted that's not saying much but, the few dishes I shared with a friend at this just two week old family operation tonight were really quite good: not too heavy or salty, well spiced.  Sweet and unpretentious service by the kids while the parents handled the back.  Reasonable prices.  Folks should really support this joint so we finally have a decent Indian place in the area!  Four stars might be a more accurate rating, but I'm giving them five to get started.  Might be BYOB for now.
